	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There are two lockouts: the CIC lockout and the PPU lockout. Like the NES, the Super NES has different PPUs in different revisions: one that generates 262 lines with NTSC color and one that generates 312 lines with PAL color. The game probably detects your PAL PPU.
<br />
<br />LJ65 for NES checks the PPU lockout to make sure players aren't cheating by using the NTSC cart on a PAL system and making the game run slower to score higher.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


